  <h2>Transport</h2>

  <p>
    Most expats in Jakarta rely on ride-hailing apps or a private driver for day-to-day travel. Self-driving is possible but Jakarta traffic is dense, road markings can be inconsistent, and parking is limited in many areas.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Grab</strong><br />
  Best for private cars and longer trips</p>

  <p><strong>Gojek</strong><br />
  Strong for short trips and motorbike rides (ojek)</p>

  <p><strong>Bluebird Taxi</strong><br />
  The most trusted metered taxi option in Jakarta; recommended when ride-hailing is not available</p>

